---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";

const pageTitle = "Full Stack & AI Developer in Vapi | Nikhil";
const pageDescription = "Hire a freelance full stack and AI developer in Vapi. MERN apps, agentic AI systems, and practical automation for business growth.";
const pageKeywords = "AI developer in Vapi, full stack developer in Vapi, MERN developer Vapi, freelance developer Vapi, agentic AI developer Gujarat";

const serviceSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Service",
  serviceType: "Full Stack and AI Development",
  areaServed: "Vapi, Gujarat, India",
  provider: {
    "@type": "Person",
    name: "Nikhil Yagik",
    url: "https://nikhilyagik.dev/developer-in-vapi"
  },
  description: pageDescription
};
---

<MainLayout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} keywords={pageKeywords} image="/logo.png">
  <main class="bg-white min-h-screen pt-28 pb-20 px-4">
    <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-sm font-medium tracking-wide text-slate-500 uppercase mb-4">Vapi Gujarat Freelance Services</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 leading-tight mb-6">Full Stack and AI Developer in Vapi for Product-Driven Teams</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        If you are looking for a reliable developer in Vapi who can build both your product and your AI features, you are in the right place.
        I work with startups, service businesses, and founders who want clean execution, clear communication, and real results.
        My core focus is full stack development using the MERN ecosystem and AI system development using LangGraph, retrieval pipelines, and LLM integrations.
        This means you do not need to hire separate freelancers for frontend, backend, and AI.
        You can work with one partner who understands how the entire system should perform in production.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-10">
        I am based in Gujarat and regularly collaborate with teams around Vapi.
        I understand the practical needs of local businesses: fast delivery, manageable costs, and software that solves operational pain.
        Whether you need a customer-facing web app, an internal dashboard, or an AI assistant that reduces repetitive work,
        I can design and build the solution end to end.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Services I Provide in Vapi</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-5">
        My work combines strong engineering fundamentals with business-focused delivery.
        As a full stack developer in Vapi, I build robust MERN applications with scalable architecture, secure authentication,
        and maintainable code structure. I handle React frontend development, API design in Node.js and Express,
        MongoDB data modeling, deployment, and post-launch support.
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-5">
        As an AI developer in Vapi, I build practical systems that can be deployed in real workflows.
        This includes agentic AI flows using LangGraph, document Q and A tools using RAG,
        and workflow automations that connect user queries to real business actions.
        If your team wants to add AI without turning your app into a fragile prototype,
        I focus on implementation quality, data handling, and production reliability.
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-slate-700 space-y-2 mb-10">
        <li>Custom MERN web applications for startups and service businesses</li>
        <li>Admin panels, booking systems, and internal operations tools</li>
        <li>Agentic AI workflows using LangGraph and tool orchestration</li>
        <li>RAG pipelines for searchable company knowledge bases</li>
        <li>API integration, deployment, performance tuning, and technical handover</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Projects That Show How I Build</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-5">
        I believe clients should evaluate developers through shipped projects, not just claims.
        One example is Servielliance, a full stack marketplace platform inspired by on-demand service models.
        The project includes user and provider workflows, booking lifecycle handling, and role-based features.
        It demonstrates how I approach real-world product complexity: clean UX, structured backend logic,
        and practical deployment decisions.
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-5">
        Another strong example is TimeCapsule, an AI-enabled app where users store and retrieve future reminders through natural language.
        This project combines product design and AI integration in a way that feels useful rather than experimental.
        It reflects the kind of automation many teams in Vapi want today: simple interface for users,
        intelligent behavior under the hood, and a backend that remains manageable for future updates.
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-10">
        I also build agentic AI systems for content generation, chat, and knowledge workflows.
        My LangGraph-based systems include multi-step planning, retrieval, and action routing,
        so the model can do meaningful work instead of producing shallow output.
        If your requirement is both a polished web product and intelligent AI capability,
        these projects demonstrate exactly that combined capability.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Why Teams in Vapi Choose to Work With Me</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-5">
        Clients usually come to me when they want fewer handoff issues and more ownership.
        Because I cover full stack and AI development together, project decisions remain aligned.
        Your frontend behavior, API architecture, and AI logic are designed as one system,
        which reduces expensive rework and timeline drift.
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-5">
        I work in a transparent, milestone-driven way.
        You get clear weekly updates, demo checkpoints, and practical suggestions based on your goals.
        I prefer measurable outcomes: faster workflow steps, improved lead handling,
        better user retention, and software that your team can confidently operate.
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-10">
        For local teams in Vapi, collaboration speed matters.
        Shared language, cultural context, and timezone alignment make execution easier.
        If you need a freelance MERN developer in Vapi or an AI developer in Gujarat who can build and deliver quickly,
        I can be a dependable technical partner.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">How We Can Work Together</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-5">
        Most projects start with a short discovery call where we define the business goal,
        key features, and a realistic delivery timeline.
        After that, I share a phased plan with milestones so you always know what is being built and why.
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-10">
        I am open to both one-time project builds and ongoing freelance collaboration.
        If you are planning a new product, modernizing an existing app, or adding AI automation to your operations,
        I can help you execute it with speed and quality.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions from Vapi Clients</h2>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Do you work with small businesses in Vapi?</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-5">
        Yes. I work with local service providers, growing startups, and founders who need practical software delivery.
        Some projects begin as focused MVPs and later scale into larger platforms.
        I can help define the right phase for your current budget and business goal, then build with a roadmap that avoids rework.
      </p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Can you build both web app and AI features in one project?</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-5">
        Absolutely. This is one of my core strengths.
        I can build your frontend and backend architecture first, then integrate AI workflows such as RAG search,
        agentic automation, and LLM-powered user flows.
        This keeps the product coherent and prevents the integration issues that happen when different vendors work in isolation.
      </p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">How do you manage delivery and communication?</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-10">
        I use milestone-based execution with regular updates, working demos, and clear priorities.
        You always know what has been completed, what is next, and what decisions are needed from your side.
        This process keeps Vapi projects predictable and helps teams launch with confidence.
      </p>

      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Ready to Hire a Developer in Vapi?</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Share your idea, target users, and current challenge. I will help you map the right full stack and AI solution,
          then build it with a delivery plan you can trust.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a href="/#contact" class="px-6 py-3 rounded-lg bg-slate-900 text-white font-medium hover:bg-slate-800 transition-colors">Hire Me</a>
          <a href="/#projects" class="px-6 py-3 rounded-lg bg-white border border-slate-300 text-slate-900 font-medium hover:bg-slate-100 transition-colors">View Projects</a>
          <a href="/developer-in-ahmedabad" class="px-6 py-3 rounded-lg bg-white border border-slate-300 text-slate-900 font-medium hover:bg-slate-100 transition-colors">Ahmedabad Page</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(serviceSchema)} />
</MainLayout>
